  "texts": [
    "Additionally, the characteristic timescale of the DRW model (τ DRW) correlates positively with M BH (e.g., Burke et al. 2021; Wang et al. 2023).",
    "These empiri-cal relations not only provide valuable insights into the physical mechanisms driving AGN variability, but also form the basis for new techniques to estimate AGN fundamental properties using photometric data alone.",
    "For example, Burke et al. (2022) leveraged the τ DRW -M BH correlation to search for low-mass AGNs powered by accreting massive black holes (MBH; 10 5 M ⊙ < M BH < 10 7 M ⊙) at the centers of dwarf galaxies (i.e., M ⋆ ≲ 10 10 M ⊙; Greene et al. 2020).",
    "AGN UV/optical variability at longer wavelengths is also often observed to lag behind the variability at shorter wavelengths (Collier et al. 1999; Sergeev et al. 2005).",
    "Under the thermal reprocessing scenario, longer-wavelength photons originate from disk annuli located farther from the central supermassive black hole (SMBH) than those emitting shorter-wavelength photons (Shakura & Sunyaev 1973)."
  ],
